RIYADH: Pilgrims departing Saudi Arabia after completing Hajj are being gifted copies of the Qur’an at Jeddah’s King Abdulaziz International Airport, Saudi Press Agency reported. One million copies of the holy book in different sizes and translations of it in 76 languages will be distributed to pilgrims leaving the Kingdom through land, sea and air ports. Hajj workers from various government sectors will also receive copies. The airport said it is preparing to bid farewell to pilgrims through three halls accommodating more than 127,000 passengers per day.